  "original_title": "162 \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0d9b\u0ddd\u0db4\u0db7\u0ddd\u0d9c\u0dd3 \u0db6\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dca\u0da2\u0db1\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "162 A Luxury Bus Strike",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The employees of Route No. 162 Bandaragama Colombo luxury bus went on a strike today (30th), saying that they have been treated unfairly due to the arbitrary implementation of two laws by the Kalutara Road Transport Authority.",
        "They staged a strike at Bandaragama Old Bus Stand by displaying protest placards on buses.",
        "\"We condemn the misdeeds of the Kalutara Passenger Transport Authority\" \"Suspended journeys will be restored\" and \"We do not want an arbitrary timetable\" were displayed on the wonderful buses.",
        "They alleged that the Kalutara Road Transport Authority is working unilaterally by allowing only 8 of the 27 licensed buses to run on the Bandaragama-Colombo route after the Corona epidemic, allowing other buses to run in garment factories and other institutions.",
        "Along with some bus owners, he alleged that the Road Transport Authority has limited eight buses by using an unfair schedule.",
        "They further accuse that the law of the jungle is applied only to the buses that run like that.",
        "They say that before the Corona season, 17 buses were running daily.",
        "The drivers say that the number of these buses plying from Bandaragama to Colombo is not enough and due to this the passengers have suffered a lot of inconvenience.",
        "They demand to implement the scheduled schedule and make arrangements to bring all the buses and run them from 5 am onwards.",
        "The drivers further said that this will provide transportation facilities to the passengers as well.",
        "When asked about this from the Acting Regional Manager of the Road Passenger Transport Authority (Kalutara), Mr. Prasanna Kure said:",
        "On the last 24th, a meeting was held in Kalutara regarding the running of luxury buses in Bandaragama, Colombo. The Road Passenger Transport Authority as an institution has made a regulation.",
        "We presented a task cycle for running buses. There are two or three conductors who are trying to get their so-called ideas to the top. That's why they are on strike.",
        "The owners of certain buses that are not running on the road have various problems. We need to look into it. According to the rules and regulations of the company, measures are taken to issue fines for the non-running time for the buses that are not running with licenses. There is no basis for this strike."
      ],
